node.text:
Ready in a few minutes, this #bread is super delicious! 
 
INGREDIENTS
900g (7 cups) flour
300ml (1 1/5 cups) warm milk
300ml (1 1/5 cups) warm water
4g (1 tsp) salt
7g dry yeast
Olive oil
Parsley

METHOD
Add flour, yeast, water, milk, and salt to the mixing bowl. Knead the dough. Leave to rest for 60 minutes.
Divide the dough into 8 parts and roll out with a rolling pin.
Bake on high heat in a pan. Coat with oil and parsley. Serve.

node.text:
These #calzones are delicious, you won't be able to stop at one! 
 
INGREDIENTS
600g (5 cups) flour
330ml (1 ¼ cups) water
10g (2 tsp) baking powder
4g (1 tsp) salt
25ml (2 tbsp) olive oil
 
Filling:
100ml (2/5 cup) tomato pasta
100g mozzarella
100g ham
100g (2/5 cup) bechamel

METHOD
In a mixing bowl add the flour, yeast, and a little water at a time, then add the salt and oil and start kneading.
Knead everything well until it forms a smooth and soft dough, then with a rolling pin roll out a sheet of about 5mm high.
With a pasta bowl, make lots of circles, stuffed with tomato and mozzarella or béchamel and cooked ham.
Then close all the panzerotti in the shape of a half-moon and seal with a fork so that the filling does not come out during cooking.
Now fry them in abundant hot oil for a couple of minutes on each side or until you see them golden. Serve.

The two-color cake is DIVINE! Everyone will ask you the recipe!

INGREDIENTS
2 eggs
60g (1/3 cup) sugar
4g (1 tsp) vanilla sugar
60ml (¼ cup) oil
120ml (½ cup) milk
250g (2 cups) flour
10g (2 tsp) baking powder
10g (1 tbsp) cocoa powder
 
METHOD
In a mixing bowl add the eggs, sugar, vanilla, oil, and milk. Mix. Add flour and baking powder. Mix well.
Pour 80% of the mixture into a baking tin.
Mix the rest of the mixture with cocoa and make tufts on the cake.
Bake at 360°F / 180°C for 25 minutes. Garnish with powdered sugar and serve.

node.text:
This method to make delicious #fritters is genius! 
 
INGREDIENTS
300g (2 3/8 cups) flour
1/3 tsp salt
40ml (3 tbsp) oil
baking powder 10g
2 eggs
2 tbsp cocoa
hazelnut cream
powdered sugar
 

METHOD
In a bowl mix together flour with salt, oil, baking powder and eggs.
Divide the dough into 2 portions and add cocoa powder to the second. Let it rest for 20 minutes.
Divide the dough into little pieces then roll out them.
Cut it into the 4 triangles and put 7-8 triangles one on top of the other along.
Roll them and cut them into 2 pieces making flowers fasten them with toothpicks.
Fry in the hot oil until golden brown.
Serve with hazelnut cream and powdered sugar.

node.text:
If you love #zucchini, this recipe is perfect for you! 
 
INGREDIENTS
2 zucchini
4g (1 tsp) salt
4g (1 tsp) paprika

For dough:
2 eggs
200g (1 cup) yogurt
200 ml (4/5 cup) milk
10g ( 2 tsp) baking powder
4g (1 tsp) salt
Dill
125g (1 cup) flour
 
For the filling:
Cheese

METHOD
Grate the zucchini and add salt and pepper. Add eggs, yogurt, milk, salt, baking powder, dill, and flour to the mixing bowl. Mix.
Pour zucchini into an oiled pan.
Put grated cheese on them and pour over the mixture.
Cover and bake. Serve.

node.text:
This is a perfect idea to make a delicious lunch for the whole family!

INGREDIENTS
500g minced meat
1 onion
1 egg
ham slices
Cheese slices
Grilled zucchini slices
1 tsp salt
1/2 tsp black pepper
3 eggs
Flour
Breadcrumbs

METHOD
Mix together minced meat with onion, egg, salt, and black pepper.
Spread the meat on cling film, top it with cherry slices, ham slices, and grilled zucchini. Wrap in a roll and freeze for 1 hour.
Cut into slices and dip into flour eggs and breadcrumbs.
Fry in the hot oil until golden brown.

node.text:
You won't be able to stop at one!

INGREDIENTS
300g hazelnut cream
120ml (½ cup) milk
7g dry yeast
50g sugar
2 eggs
Oil
1 lime zest
260g (2 cups) flour
 
Sugar for coating
 
METHOD
Pour the hazelnut cream into small portions on the parchment paper. Leave in the freezer for 1-2 hours.
 
Dissolve the dry yeast and sugar in the milk. Add the eggs, oil, lime zest, flour and mix well.
 
Take portions of the batter with a spoon and fill them with the cold hazelnut cream.
 
Fry the mixture in boiling oil until golden.
 
Dip the pancakes in sugar and serve.

node.text:
Here're 2 amazing ideas with #tortilla!

INGREDIENTS
Tortillas
4 eggs
50g (1/2 cup) shredded cheese
1/2 tsp salt
1/3 tsp pepper
1/3 red bell pepper
1/3 yellow pepper
1/3 green pepper
80ml (1/3 cup) sour cream
 
METHOD
Make circles on tortillas by using a glass or a plate. Transfer them to a baking pan.
Mix eggs with species and shredded cheese, pour the mixture into the tortilla cups, add chopped peppers.
Bake at 180’C (350’F) for 5 minutes, sprinkle with shredded cheese and bake for 4 minutes more.
Add egg mixture to a pan and cover with tortilla, fry from both sides. Wrap it in the roll.

node.text:
Perfect for a tasty dinner, this #focaccia is ready in a few steps!

INGREDIENTS
60ml (1/4 cup) water
7g dry yeast
250g (2 cups) flour
8g (2 tsp) sugar
4g (1 tsp) salt
10ml (2 tsp) olive oil
120ml (½ cup) milk
Butter
Cheese

METHOD
In a small bowl, pour water, yeast, sugar, and a spoonful of flour.
Leave to rise for 15 minutes.
Pour flour, salt and yeast mixture into a mixing bowl. Add milk and knead the dough.
Drizzle the dough with oil and knead until combined. Leave to stand for 60 minutes.
Divide into four parts and fill with butter and cheese.
Bake in a pan. Serve.

node.text:
With zucchini, eggs and potatoes you can make a delicious dinner in no-time! 
 
INGREDIENTS
3 medium potatoes
1 zucchini
2 eggs (1 for the omelette & 1 for the fritters)
6 g (1 tsp) salt
60 ml (4 tbsp) vegetable oil (divided, for frying)
2 g (2 tsp) parsley, chopped (divided, optional)
60g (2 oz) mozzarella, shredded

METHOD
Grate potatoes and zucchini and transfer to the strainer to remove any excess liquids.
Place strained flesh into a bowl and season with salt.
Add an egg and mix well.
Heat a tablespoon of oil in a frying pan. Place 3-4 tablespoons of potato-zucchini mixture and form a round fritter.
Cook it for 2-3 minutes or until golden, then flip and make a hole in the middle with a small spoon.
Add an egg into the hole. Cover with a lid and cook until the desired doneness of the egg yolk.
Season with salt and sprinkle chopped parsley on top (optional).
Add one more tablespoon of oil to the frying pan. Form small round fritters from the remaining mixture and cook on both sides until golden.
When almost cooked, top each fritter with shredded cheese, cover with a lid and cook on low until cheese melts.
Sprinkle some chopped parsley on top (optional) and serve immediately.

node.text:
This method is genius, put them in a plate!

INGREDIENTS
2 eggs
120g (1/2 cup) yogurt
1/3 tsp salt
1 tsp vanilla extract
100g (1/2 cup) sugar
1 tbsp oil
1 tsp baking powder
2 cups flour ( 260g )
Melted chocolate for topping
 
METHOD
In a bowl mix together eggs with yogurt, salt, vanilla extract, oil, sugar, baking powder and flour.
Make a bowl using a plate.
Fry them in hot oil.
Serve with melted chocolate.

node.text:
Ready in a few minutes, this #bread is super delicious! 
 
INGREDIENTS
900g (7 cups) flour
300ml (1 1/5 cups) warm milk
300ml (1 1/5 cups) warm water
4g (1 tsp) salt
7g dry yeast
Olive oil
Parsley

METHOD
Add flour, yeast, water, milk, and salt to the mixing bowl. Knead the dough. Leave to rest for 60 minutes.
Divide the dough into 8 parts and roll out with a rolling pin.
Bake on high heat in a pan. Coat with oil and parsley. Serve.

node.text:
These #calzones are delicious, you won't be able to stop at one! 
 
INGREDIENTS
600g (5 cups) flour
330ml (1 ¼ cups) water
10g (2 tsp) baking powder
4g (1 tsp) salt
25ml (2 tbsp) olive oil
 
Filling:
100ml (2/5 cup) tomato pasta
100g mozzarella
100g ham
100g (2/5 cup) bechamel

METHOD
In a mixing bowl add the flour, yeast, and a little water at a time, then add the salt and oil and start kneading.
Knead everything well until it forms a smooth and soft dough, then with a rolling pin roll out a sheet of about 5mm high.
With a pasta bowl, make lots of circles, stuffed with tomato and mozzarella or béchamel and cooked ham.
Then close all the panzerotti in the shape of a half-moon and seal with a fork so that the filling does not come out during cooking.
Now fry them in abundant hot oil for a couple of minutes on each side or until you see them golden. Serve.

node.text:
The two-color cake is DIVINE! Everyone will ask you the recipe!

INGREDIENTS
2 eggs
60g (1/3 cup) sugar
4g (1 tsp) vanilla sugar
60ml (¼ cup) oil
120ml (½ cup) milk
250g (2 cups) flour
10g (2 tsp) baking powder
10g (1 tbsp) cocoa powder
 
METHOD
In a mixing bowl add the eggs, sugar, vanilla, oil, and milk. Mix. Add flour and baking powder. Mix well.
Pour 80% of the mixture into a baking tin.
Mix the rest of the mixture with cocoa and make tufts on the cake.
Bake at 360°F / 180°C for 25 minutes. Garnish with powdered sugar and serve.

node.text:
This method to make delicious #fritters is genius! 
 
INGREDIENTS
300g (2 3/8 cups) flour
1/3 tsp salt
40ml (3 tbsp) oil
baking powder 10g
2 eggs
2 tbsp cocoa
hazelnut cream
powdered sugar
 

METHOD
In a bowl mix together flour with salt, oil, baking powder and eggs.
Divide the dough into 2 portions and add cocoa powder to the second. Let it rest for 20 minutes.
Divide the dough into little pieces then roll out them.
Cut it into the 4 triangles and put 7-8 triangles one on top of the other along.
Roll them and cut them into 2 pieces making flowers fasten them with toothpicks.
Fry in the hot oil until golden brown.
Serve with hazelnut cream and powdered sugar.

A funny and original way to serve #melon!
This idea is so cute, kids will love it!

INGREDIENTS
Melon
Blueberries
Peppercorns
Toothpicks

METHOD
Cut one edge of the whole melon. Make two small cuts and fit two circles of the same shell. Make two small holes and add two pepper balls to form eyes.
Use a spherical fruit cutter to get balls from the melon pulp. Cut the melon in half and remove the pulp.
Pour the balls in the middle of the melon and decorate with the rind in the form of a mouse face.
and then decorate with blueberries.

node.text:
You only need a few ingredients to make the fluffiest #brioche ever! 

INGREDIENTS
200ml (3/4 cup + 2 tbsp) warm water;
7g (2 tsp) dry yeast;
350g (2 cups) all-purpose flour;
50g (1/4 cup) sugar;
½ tsp salt;
45g (3 tbsp) butter.
METHOD
Whisk warm water with sugar and dry yeast. Set them aside for the yeast to activate.
Wisk the flour with salt and pour the yeast solution in.
Work the dough with your hands until combined, then add butter and knead for 10 minutes.
Set the ball of dough aside for 2 hours.
Cut the dough into 6 pieces, roll each one out and roll again into a log.
Place logs into the cake pan and set aside for 1 hour or until doubled.
Bake for 20-25 minutes at 180°C/350°F.

node.text:
If you love #zucchini, this recipe is perfect for you! 
 
INGREDIENTS
2 zucchini
4g (1 tsp) salt
4g (1 tsp) paprika

For dough:
2 eggs
200g (1 cup) yogurt
200 ml (4/5 cup) milk
10g ( 2 tsp) baking powder
4g (1 tsp) salt
Dill
125g (1 cup) flour
 
For the filling:
Cheese

METHOD
Grate the zucchini and add salt and pepper. Add eggs, yogurt, milk, salt, baking powder, dill, and flour to the mixing bowl. Mix.
Pour zucchini into an oiled pan.
Put grated cheese on them and pour over the mixture.
Cover and bake. Serve.
